title: Kennedy.2015.07.23.WS.SDTV.x264-XAiO
description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Tonight Kennedy does her monologue on a recently released Prince song about Freddie Gray and some anti-gun lyrics contained within.

Tonight we welcome to the panel MICHAEL MALICE, WILL RAHN, and KIRSTEN HAGLUND. First topic - The GAO says IRS political targeting is indeed possible under current regulation despite claims to the contrary by Obama. Next up, Anthony Weiner joins communications firm.

Our panel returns to talk about Mark Zuckerberg and his estimated networth of 43 billion dollars. Kennedy asks the panel what they would do with that amount of money. Now - The sharing economy is starting to cover doctors. Get medical care with an iPhone app. 

JOHN BOLTON is here to talk about the growing threat of Americans radicalized by ISIS propaganda. Over blown threat or something to worry about? (Guess what John's opinion is.) Bolton uses the word "intrusive" when describing what he thinks out cyber security efforts should be like.

Topical Storm:
Man gets inside giant balloon, fills it with water until it pops.
Ashley Madison hacked, details starting to leak out.
Cory Feldman plays Michael Jackson cover concert at baseball game. Baseball team apologizes.
Man caught smoking on google maps.
Magpie loves marijuana.

The panel is back to talk about how Hillary Clinton fares when polled against her husband Bill. She wins handily. Afterwards they talk about Prince's new protest song and its anti-gun lyrics. Next - Australian academic says that we need to be afraid of aliens.

JIMMY PARDO is in studio to talk about his new show "Race to Escape" on the science channel.

Nightcap! MAILBAG!
